SUMMARY:Animal Law Week
DESCRIPTION:*Events that are open to the public are shown with an asteris
 k.MONDAY\, MARCH 9 12:10-1:10 PM PST McCARTY ROOM 3 and ONLINE*  Join the
  Center for Animal Law Studies for this special event to kick off Animal 
 Law Week. In 2024\, Lucy's Project convened a National Roundtable on Dome
 stic and Family Violence Perpetrated against People and Animals. This pre
 sentation will share the Roundtable findings and recommendations for legi
 slative\, policy and program reform to improve the safety and wellbeing o
 f people and animals across Australia. Vegan lunch provided! To join onli
 ne\, RSVP here (https://lclark-edu.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_bQ-9uYo-S7
 GzynykmuTbVQ#/registration).TUESDAY\, MARCH 10 12:10-1 PM PST LRC LOUNGE 
  Join LC ALDF for the annual MeatOut event. MeatOut celebrates Portland's
  vegan food scene and encourages our campus community to consider plant-b
 ased options. Food will be available on a first-come\, first-served basis
 . To reduce waste\, please bring your own tupperware and serve yourself o
 nly as much food as you will eat.THURSDAY\, MARCH 12 12:10-1:10 PM PST Mc
 CARTY ROOM 3  Join LC ALDF for Taking Individual Action for Animals\, a m
 ultimedia exploration of the history of the animal liberation movement. T
 his talk will highlight key events to show how early activists demanded c
 hange and impacted the modern scope of animal advocacy. This event is a p
 relude to LC ALDF's evening reception.THURSDAY\, MARCH 12 7-9 PM PST LRC 
 LOUNGE*  Join LC ALDF for the annual Animal Law Week reception featuring 
 animal activist Zoe Rosenberg\, who was sentenced to 90 days in jail for 
 rescuing 4 sick chickens from a slaughterhouse. Through discussion\, hist
 orical artifacts\, and community\, explore how open rescue challenges ind
 ustrial animal agriculture and advances justice for animals. Refreshments
  provided by Vtopian Artisan Cheeses. There will also be a silent auction
  benefiting Lighthouse Farm Sanctuary. RSVP here. (https://engage.lclark.
 edu/register/AnimalLawWeekReception2026)&#160\;
