SUMMARY:Awakened Awareness
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Spring Cohort begins Jan. 29 and will conclude befor
 e spring break on Mar. 18. Our finale on March 18th will include a celebr
 ation of all we have learned and feature requested treats! We want partic
 ipants to be able to make all the sessions\, as each session builds upon 
 the last. We also recognize that sickness and other unplanned things happ
 en\, and so hope that participants can make a minimum of 6/8 workshops.  
 Each session includes an opening meditation\, journaling\, peer-to-peer s
 haring\, a weekly "focus\," a special guided meditation\, group sharing\,
  and a closing meditation. Participants are also provided journals.&#160\
 ;  Our Spring 2026 Monday Cohort will be facilitated by Hilary Martin Him
 an (Center for Spiritual Life) and Theresa Brostowitz (Campus Living.)  A
 wakened Awareness is a science-driven\, meditation-based series of worksh
 ops that was developed from research at Columbia University's Teachers Co
 llege and the work of Dr. Lisa Miller\, and has been conducted there with
  undergraduates for years with positive results. More colleges and univer
 sities across the country are now offering it to their own undergraduate 
 students.  If you have a disability and/or require accommodations\, pleas
 e email us ahead of time at hmhiman@lclark.edu so that we may assist you 
 as best possible.  Questions about what to expect? Please reach out to Hi
 lary\, hmhiman@lclark.edu (mailto:hmhiman@lclark.edu) or call 503-768-708
 2.&#160\;  Open to Lewis &amp\; Clark undergrad and graduate students.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The 2026 Spring Cohort begins <strong>J
 an. 29</strong> and will conclude before spring break on <strong>Mar. 18<
 /strong>. Our finale on March 18th will include a celebration of all we h
 ave learned and feature requested treats! We want participants to be able
  to make all the sessions\, as each session builds upon the last. We also
  recognize that sickness and other unplanned things happen\, and so hope 
 that participants can make a minimum of 6/8 workshops.</p><p>  Each sessi
 on includes an opening meditation\, journaling\, peer-to-peer sharing\, a
  weekly "focus\," a special guided meditation\, group sharing\, and a clo
 sing meditation. Participants are also provided journals.&#160\;</p><p>  
 Our Spring 2026 Monday Cohort will be facilitated by Hilary Martin Himan 
 (Center for Spiritual Life) and Theresa Brostowitz (Campus Living.)</p><p
 >  Awakened Awareness is a science-driven\, meditation-based series of wo
 rkshops that was developed from research at Columbia University's Teacher
 s College and the work of Dr. Lisa Miller\, and has been conducted there 
 with undergraduates for years with positive results. More colleges and un
 iversities across the country are now offering it to their own undergradu
 ate students.</p><p>  If you have a disability and/or require accommodati
 ons\, please email us ahead of time at hmhiman@lclark.edu so that we may 
 assist you as best possible.</p><p>  Questions about what to expect? Plea
 se reach out to Hilary\, <a href="mailto:hmhiman@lclark.edu">hmhiman@lcla
 rk.edu</a> or call 503-768-7082.&#160\;</p><p>  Open to Lewis &amp\; Clar
 k undergrad and graduate students.</p>
