SUMMARY:Board Games for 50-Somethings!
DESCRIPTION:Portland Area Board Games and RPGs\n***INTRODUCING*** modern board games to those 50 and older! Today's modern board games are typically designed to keep all players in the game until it ends\, and offer many different paths to victory. Interested in learning and playing modern board games? Come on down! This is a safe place to stretch your mind and mingle.\n\nThere will be some games available\, but if you have a favorite\, bring it with you! Be sure to RSVP and let us know if you're bringing a game in the comments\, or if you have any questions or game preferences. These are light- to medium-weight games. The objective here is to give older folks a safe environment for learning new games\, and playing their favorites!\n\nTo be clear\, these should be light- to mid-weight gateway games. Weight is determined by BoardGameGeek website complexity ratings. (*Gateway games are games that introduce one to the hobby and get them hooked on playing!*)\n\nGame night is scheduled every other week and entrance is free! Please RSVP! It's been my experience if no one signs up\, no one shows up. If there is at least ONE individual signed up I will be there!!\n\n**A brief message about ground rules:**\n\n* ***Try your best to be on time. Otherwise\, you may have to wait until a new - or another - game is starting.***\n* ***Please respect game components with clean hands and gentle touch.***\n* ***Discrimination of any kind and trash-talking will not be tolerated. (Please also refrain from engaging in politics while at the game table.)***\n* ***Start what you finish\, even if it looks like you're going to lose. "It's not the destination\, it's the journey" - Ralph Waldo Emerson. Also\, errors will be made\, above all else\, remember\, it's only a game!***\n\nAdult children under 50 are welcome to bring parent(s) with them!\n\nIn the meantime\, feel free to come and go as needed. Look for the sign\, "50 Somethings Game Night". Introduce yourself and say Hi!\n\nWelcome "a-board"!
