CREATED:20250915T181355Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T191956Z
UID:10005524-1773343800-1773349200@literary-arts.org
SUMMARY:Everybody Reads 2026: Justice Ketanji Brown Jackson (SOLD OUT)
DESCRIPTION:Literary Arts is proud to present the culminating event of Multnomah County Library’s Everybody Reads program on March 12\, 2026\, with Justice Ketanji Brown Jackson\, at the Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall. Justice Jackson will be joined in conversation by author Renée Watson. \nBAG POLICY FOR THIS EVENT: \nGuests may bring clear plastic bags only\, not to exceed 12” x 12” x 6.” No purses\, briefcases\, or large bags will be allowed inside the venue. Hand held items like wallets and phones are ok. No outside food and drink allowed. Please bring valid ID. \nExceptions to this policy include: \n\nMedical bags (subject to inspection)\nMobility/accessibility items (subject to inspection)\n\n\nJustice Jackson’s Lovely One: A Memoir is the 2026 pick for the library’s signature community reading project that promotes shared reading and discussion around a single book. Justice Jackson’s appearance will conclude months of engaging library programs and events surrounding the book and its themes such as identity\, ambition\, and resilience\, highlighting the importance of mentorship and perseverance through professional and personal challenges. \nThe Library will distribute 8\,000 free copies of Lovely One through libraries and high schools across Multnomah County beginning in January 2026\, through the generosity of The Library Foundation (while supplies last). Discounted copies of Lovely One will be available from the Literary Arts Bookstore as well as other independent bookstores around Portland. \n  \n  \n\nThis event is currently sold out. Please be careful when purchasing tickets through sites other than Portland’5 and be mindful of secondary-market ticket sites. If you have not accessed purchasing tickets directly through portland5.com\, you may be subject to increased ticket prices and fees\, and unless the ticket is verified through Portland’5 it may not be valid for entry.  \n \n 
URL:https://literary-arts.org/event/everybody-reads-2026-justice-ketanji-brown-jackson/
LOCATION:Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall\, 1037 SW Broadway\, Portland\, OR\, 97205\, United States
CATEGORIES:Ticketed Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://literary-arts.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ER-26_Custom-Book-Cover_cmyk_FPO-scaled.png
GEO:45.516856;-122.6811861
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall 1037 SW Broadway Portland OR 97205 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=1037 SW Broadway:geo:-122.6811861,45.516856
