X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lewis Clark": "https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/event/380743-transgressors-exhibit-and-symposium-closing"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lewis_clark
X-SOURCE:Lewis Clark
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T183000
LOCATION:Hoffman Gallery
GEO:45.45054;-122.668438
SUMMARY:Transgressors Exhibit and Symposium Closing Reception
DESCRIPTION:We will gather to honor forms of resistance that sustain us: 
 the everyday acts of refusal\, the radical creativity that nourishes move
 ments\, and the steadfast bravery of stories that need to be told. The co
 llaboration invites us to consider how Indigiqueer artists enact the very
  coalitional solidarities the symposium calls us to cultivate and examine
 —reminding us that art can be an act of resistance\, a practice of endu
 rance\, and a way of imagining futures worth fighting for.  Come curious\
 , ready to celebrate the power we hold together\, and primed to make a ne
 w friend and eat a snack.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  We will gather to honor forms of resist
 ance that sustain us: the everyday acts of refusal\, the radical creativi
 ty that nourishes movements\, and the steadfast bravery of stories that n
 eed to be told. The collaboration invites us to consider how Indigiqueer 
 artists enact the very coalitional solidarities the symposium calls us to
  cultivate and examine—reminding us that art can be an act of resistanc
 e\, a practice of endurance\, and a way of imagining futures worth fighti
 ng for.</p><p>  Come curious\, ready to celebrate the power we hold toget
 her\, and primed to make a new friend and eat a snack.</p>
