BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Reed College": "https://events.reed.edu/event/biology-seminar-dr-kelly-chacon"}
X-SOURCE-ID:reed_college
X-SOURCE:Reed College
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Adventures in x-ray Absorption Spectroscopy\n\nThe structural a
 nd chemical characterization of metal-containing proteins has long been of 
 importance in the realms of green chemistry\, energy and food production\, 
 environmental remediation\, antibiotic resistance\, and medicine. However\,
  structural details regarding the active site metals can sometimes be error
  prone or poorly resolved. The technique of x-ray absorption spectroscopy  
 (XAS) and Extended x-ray Absorption Fine Structure (EXAFS) on dilute\, meta
 l-containing biological molecules can provide a wealth of electronic\, inor
 ganic\, biological\, and kinetic information. In this seminar I will discus
 s some of the most interesting ways I have applied this technique to a vari
 ety of systems\, such as Zinc and Heme-sensing proteins\, Fe-S cluster prot
 eins\, and the elucidation of the human mucin Muc2 that is believed to be r
 esponsible for Cu uptake in the human gut. I will also discuss my ongoing b
 iochemical project to determine the mechanism of resistance and reduction o
 f toxic Te ions to elemental Te in bacteria. \n\nDr. Chacón is a high schoo
 l dropout who worked in the service industry for a decade and received a GE
 D from Clatsop Community College in Astoria Oregon in 2003. Kelly then went
  on to earn a B.S. in Chemistry and Biochemistry at Portland State Universi
 ty in 2009 and a Ph.D. in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology at OHSU in 201
 5. Kelly is currently the Arthur F. Scott Associate Professor of Chemistry 
 at Reed College in Portland\, Oregon.\n\n11:50 am- Snacks & Socializing\nno
 on- Talk Begins
DTEND:20260313T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260312T160904Z
DTSTART:20260313T190000Z
GEO:45.480779;-122.627995
LOCATION:Biology\, 19
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Biology Seminar: Dr. Kelly Chacón
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52278133195070
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/biology-seminar-dr-kelly-chacon
END:VEVENT
