BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Reed College": "https://events.reed.edu/event/politics-and-post-kantian-thought-judgment-knowledge-and-the-state"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Reed College": "https://events.reed.edu/event/politics-and-post-kantian-thought-judgment-knowledge-and-the-state"}
X-SOURCE-ID:reed_college
X-SOURCE:Reed College
CATEGORIES:Conference/Symposium,Lecture
DESCRIPTION:An international cohort of eminent scholars will convene for a 
 symposium dedicated to exploring questions of political judgment\, politica
 l epistemology\, and the nature and role of the state\, as framed within an
 d through post-Kantian thought.\n\nThe symposium honors Peter Steinberger’s
  distinguished intellectual career and the enduring influence of his nearly
  five decades (and counting!) of teaching and scholarship on generations of
  students and scholars. \n\nThe event will open with a keynote address on F
 riday evening and continue on Saturday with a day-long conference comprisin
 g three sequential panels. Each panel will feature three substantial papers
  presented by leading scholars representing a range of disciplines\, includ
 ing philosophy\, political theory\, history\, and literature. A volume of s
 elected papers and commentary from the symposium will be published in a lea
 ding academic journal. Reed College faculty\, alumni\, and members of the b
 roader academic community are invited to attend.\n\n \n\nKeynote Address: “
 Welcome to the Unicontext”\nAgnes Callard\, Department of Philosophy\, Univ
 ersity of Chicago\nFriday\, March 13\, 2026\n5:00 p.m. \nVollum lecture hal
 l\n\n \n\nPanels\nSaturday\, March 14\, 2026\nPerforming Arts Building 320\
 n\n9:30 - 11:15 a.m.\n“Kantian and Post-Kantian Applications”\nPanelists: L
 isa Ellis\, Ōtākou Whakaihu Waka / University of Otago\; Susan Shell\, Bost
 on College\; Alan Patten\, Princeton University\; Peter Gordon\, Harvard Un
 iversity\nDiscussant: Josh Simon\, Johns Hopkins University\n\n12:45 - 2:15
  p.m.\n“Political Possibilities of Hegel and Heidegger”\nPanelists: Brandon
  Hogan\, Howard University\; Richard Wolin\, CUNY Graduate Center\; Peter S
 teinberger\, Reed College\nDiscussant: Liz Wingrove\, University of Michiga
 n \n\n2:30 - 4:00 p.m.\n“Political Judgment and Political Leadership”\nPane
 lists: Steven Smith\, Yale University\; Ronnie Beiner\, University of Toron
 to\; Linda Zerilli\, University of Chicago\nDiscussant: Ophelia Vedder\, Wa
 shington University\n\n \n\nSponsored by the Greenberg Distinguished Schola
 r Program and the department of political science. Free and open to the pub
 lic.
DTEND:20260314T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260312T160904Z
DTSTART:20260314T000000Z
GEO:45.480983;-122.634105
LOCATION:Performing Arts Building
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Politics and Post-Kantian Thought: Judgment\, Knowledge\, and the S
 tate
