SUMMARY: The Life of Galileo
DESCRIPTION:Mt Hood Repertory Theatre is excited to announce that our pro
 duction of The Life of Galileo by Bertolt Brecht\, adapted and directed b
 y Patrick Walsh\, will be at OMSI in the Kendall Planetarium. Our product
 ion of Silent Sky by Lauren Gunderson was such a success last year that O
 MSI has invited us back.\n\nThis will be the third play performed in OMSI
 ’s Kendall planetarium in its history and the third time worldwide that T
 he Life of Galileo has been performed in a planetarium!\n\nThe performanc
 e includes stunning celestial visuals designed by OMSI Planetarium direct
 or Jim Todd\, music performed live by Adrian Harris Crowne\, and glorious
  period costumes by Daisy Irskin\n\nThe Life of Galileo delves into the s
 tory of Galileo Galilei\, a scientist speaking truth to power in a world 
 that doesn’t believe in science.
CATEGORIES:theater,performance
