UID:10001345-1773482400-1773498600@portlandartmuseum.org
SUMMARY:Level Up Your Magic the Gathering Game Play
DESCRIPTION:Cost $65Ages 11-14\, limited to 20 participants \n\n\n\nIn this hands-on workshop for youth ages 11–14\, participants will learn to play Magic: The Gathering (MTG) while investigating the strategy\, systems\, and creative thinking of the game. Game Designer and Master of Magic Sasha Jelten will mentor hands-on matches and play-based learning\, helping participants learn core mechanics like casting spells\, summoning creatures\, managing resources\, and navigating turns while building confidence as emerging players. \n\n\n\nParticipants will also dive into deck building by analyzing cards\, testing ideas\, and refining strategies to create effective\, personalized decks. Along the way\, MTG becomes a tool for design thinking as players plan\, prototype\, playtest\, and iterate\, learning how intentional choices shape big outcomes. \n\n\n\nParticipants are welcome to bring their own MTG cards\, but no supplies are needed. With the support of our partners at The Portland Game Store and the non-profit MagiKids\, we’ll have cards and game resources for participants to use and take home.  \n\n\n\n This fun\, imaginative workshop invites young players to think like designers\, play like strategists\, and take home the cards and skills to keep their Magic: The Gathering adventures going strong.  \n\n\n\nWhy Join? Along the way\, players strengthen real-world skills woven into gameplay: strategic thinking\, collaboration\, resilience\, and sportsmanship. Friendly matches encourage communication\, empathy\, and emotional awareness as players celebrate wins\, learn from losses\, and support one another. \n\n\n\n\nregister for level up your magic the gathering\n\n\n\n\nAbout the teaching artist\n\n\n\n\n\nSasha Jelten is a Portland based board game designer and founder of Playtest PDX\, a local game design group. Sasha spends most of his time playtesting games\, hosting events\, making food\, and playing Magic the Gathering.
URL:https://portlandartmuseum.org/event/level-up-your-magic-the-gathering-game-play/
LOCATION:PAM CUT\, 934 SW Salmon St.\, Portland\, OR\, 97205
CATEGORIES:Classes & camps
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://portlandartmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2_MAR-2026-YAU-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
