SUMMARY:Senior Degree Recital: Milo Hodges
DESCRIPTION:This recital presents Romantic and 20th-century repertoire fo
 r the classical guitar. The program includes La Catedral by Agustín Barr
 ios Mangoré\, selections by Francisco Tárrega\, and works by Astor Piaz
 zolla. Also featured is a piece written by Michael Stirling\, rooted in I
 ndian classical music traditions. The program highlights the development 
 from Romantic traditions to the rhythmic and stylistic innovations of Nue
 vo Tango\, showcasing a wide range of expressive possibilities within the
  instrument's repertoire.  This performance will be live streamed here. (
 https://vimeo.com/event/4079258)  &#160\;Parking at Lewis &amp\; Clark - 
 For events in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, or Diane Gregg P
 avilion\, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswold\, Lower Griswold\, o
 r Fir Acres Lots (see: campus map (https://www.lclark.edu/live/files/7676
 -campus-map)).Parking permits are required during the academic year betwe
 en Monday through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see the Visiting Campus pag
 e (https://www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transportation/visitor_parkin
 g/) for additional details. For weekday events before 7pm\, visitors may 
 purchase day passes online (https://lclark.t2hosted.com/Account/Portal) o
 r via QR codes posted in all major parking lots.
