 >gssart@lclark.edu</a>\n</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  One important part of the symposium is an art 
 exhibit of work from community members from Lewis &amp\; Clark and beyond
 . The <a href="https://college.lclark.edu/departments/gender_studies/symp
 osium/45th-annual-gender-studies-symposium/" target="_blank" rel="noopene
 r">45th Annual Gender Studies Symposium</a>\, "RESIST NOW\," explores dim
 ensions of resistance\, activism\, and solidarity in relation to gender a
 nd sexuality<br />\n  <br />\n  This year's exhibit includes a gallery in
  the Watzek Library atrium and an online gallery.\n</p>\n<p>\n  Curated b
 y L&amp\;C students <strong>Jamison Bane</strong> '27\, <strong>Finn Dwye
 r</strong> '28\, and <strong>Maria Martinez Decuir</strong> '27.\n</p>
