SUMMARY:Sunday Long Run from PRC NW
DESCRIPTION:Portland Running Co. Weekly Group Runs\nPortland Running Company leads a long run every Sunday morning departing from our location at 2258 NW Raleigh St. in Portland.\n\nWe decide the route(s) on the spot\; there is almost always a contingent heading into Forest Park to hit the trails. Other routes we like include Terwilliger/Council Crest\, Mount Tabor\, and the Sellwood Bridge Loop. Distances vary\, but most folks run for about two hours.\n\nIf you've never run with PRC before\, you may need to sign a waiver beforehand. (No dogs\, please.) Free and open to all\, like all of PRC's Group Runs. More info and waiver here: https://portlandrunning.com/pages/weekly-group-runs
