SUMMARY:Call for Papers: 2026 Dorothy Berkson Writing Award in Gender Stu
 dies
DESCRIPTION:17th Annual Dorothy Berkson Writing Award in Gender Studies  
 &#160\;  This award recognizes written achievement (e.g.\, scholarly essa
 ys\, research projects\, creative non-fiction\, fiction\, poetry\, or pla
 ywriting) focused on gender and authored by a senior.  A monetary prize a
 ccompanies the award.  The award winners will present their papers at a r
 eception on April 18\, 2025 (https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/even
 t/354223-2024-reception-for-dorothy-berkson-writing-award) that celebrate
 s their work. The presentation will be recorded for archival purposes. Th
 ese awards are given in memory of Dorothy Berkson\, professor emerita of 
 English who taught at Lewis &amp\; Clark from 1981 until her retirement i
 n 2004.Submissions due by 5 p.m.Friday\, March 21\, 2025  &#160\;Submissi
 ons may come from any field of study as long as gender is central to the 
 work. The author must be a graduating senior in 24-25. Most often the wor
 k will be produced in the senior year\, but outstanding work from one's j
 unior year will also be considered.  Submissions (maximum 5\,000 words) m
 ust be accompanied by a faculty recommendation that provides context for 
 the work and speaks to its merits.  Awardees will be determined by a facu
 lty committee  Student submissions use this link (https://forms.gle/SshBH
 XoezQbmZS4R6) to a Google form  Faculty recommendations use this link (ht
 tps://forms.gle/NtqhfPnCQJyuYam36) to a Google form    &#160\;Professor B
 erkson was a presenter in Lewis &amp\; Clark's first Gender Studies Sympo
 sium. For the gender studies minor\, she designed a course titled Gender 
 and Aesthetic Expression\, which she continued to teach for many years.  
 &#160\;Info about past awardees (https://www.lclark.edu/departments/gende
 r_studies/dorothy-berkson-writing-award/dorthy-berkson-award-archive/)
