BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Portland City Walking": "https://www.meetup.com/portland-city-walking-and-trail-walking-meetup-group/events/313734783/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_portland_city_walking
X-SOURCE:Meetup Portland City Walking
UID:event_313734783@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260312T160926Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T123000
SUMMARY:Southwest Portland Rectangular Adventure
DESCRIPTION:Portland City Trail Walking Group\n**Think you know Southwest Portland? Think again. Beneath all those windy streets and confusing intersections\, there’s actually a sneaky network of trails zig-zagging through ravines\, parks\, and neighborhoods — and we’re going to connect the dots.**\n\n**We’ll form a rough rectangle (because circles are overrated)\, starting north on Southwest Trail #7\, cutting east on #4\, then south on #6\, and finally west on #5 until we reconnect with #7 to close the loop - er\, rectangle.**\n\n**Expect a mix of quiet city streets\, where you’ll doubt they ever lead anywhere\, plus a few “shortcuts” that prove otherwise.**\n\n**Along the way\, we’ll meander through Multnomah Village\, Marshall Park\, Maricara Nature Park\, and Woods Memorial Nature Park — basically Portland’s greatest hits of “wait\, I didn’t know this was here.” We’ll even cross I‑5 twice (safely\, via overpasses\, not parkour).**\n\n**The stats: 6.5 miles\, about 700 feet of elevation gain\, 2½ hours of adventure give or take\, depending on how easily we’re distracted by plants and viewpoints.**\n\n**Meet at SW Carson & SW 42nd — plenty of street parking and no excuses. Bring water\, sun protection (wishful thinking?) or raingear\, and your best “look\, a hidden trail!” enthusiasm. This is a rain or shine event\, so think positive thoughts for glorious weather.**\n\n**Questions? Send me a message before I wander off.**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/portland-city-walking-and-trail-walking-meetup-group/events/313734783/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260310T231157Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T231157Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/a/b/2/600_532767314.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lan Su Garden": "https://lansugarden.org/event/plant-wednesday-spotlight/2026-03-18/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lan_su_garden
X-SOURCE:Lan Su Garden
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T113000
DTSTAMP:20260312T090915
CREATED:20250819T214828Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T232114Z
UID:10000760-1773831600-1773833400@lansugarden.org
SUMMARY:#PlantWednesday Spotlight
DESCRIPTION:Join our horticulture team every Wednesday for a tour diving into a plant in its peak\, gardening tips\, and more. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWednesdays\, 11-11:30 AM | Free with admission or membership \n\n\n\nThe #PlantWednesday Spotlight is a unique “show & tell” program featuring different captivating topics every month. Meet Lan Su’s horticulture team each Wednesday to explore\, learn\, and connect with the natural beauty of Lan Su. These are short 30-min sessions that showcase a horticultural wonder\, technique\, or tool that our passionate horticulturists want to share with fellow plant enthusiasts. Each session will shine a light on the behind-the-scenes operations of the garden\, highlight a plant at its peak beauty\, or focus on recent improvements to our collection. \n\n\n\nEach session will explore a different part of the garden based on that week’s topic. When you arrive\, please check in with the front door staff or volunteers for the exact location to meet in. \n\n\n\n\nGet Admission\n\n\n\n\nThis program is FREE with garden admission or membership. No registration needed.
URL:https://lansugarden.org/event/plant-wednesday-spotlight/2026-03-18/
LOCATION:Lan Su Chinese Garden\, 239 NW Everett Street\, Portland\, Oregon\, 97209
CATEGORIES:Free with admission or membership,Horticulture,Tours
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://lansugarden.org/wp-content/uploads/PlantWednesday-Spotlight-hidden-garden.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Lan Su Chinese Garden":MAILTO:info@lansugarden.org
END:VEVENT
