BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lewis Clark": "https://www.lclark.edu/live/events/386361-budget-forum"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lewis_clark
X-SOURCE:Lewis Clark
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T150000
LOCATION:Miller Hall - Room 105
GEO:45.450858;-122.668265
SUMMARY:Budget Forum
DESCRIPTION:The forum will address the actions taken in advance of the FY
 27 fiscal year to reduce expenses in the College of Arts and Science and 
 Common Services.  "These decisions were guided by several core principles
 : fulfillment of our academic mission\; a commitment to centering student
 s and equitable access\; caring for our people\; advancing the strategic 
 imperatives\; and\, a focus on community engagement and transparency\," P
 resident Holmes-Sullivan said in an email sent March 6 to all employees. 
 "While this is a challenging time in CAS and Common Services\, it is vita
 l that we come together as a community and move forward with hope\, compa
 ssion and strength."
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The forum will address the actions take
 n in advance of the FY27 fiscal year to reduce expenses in the College of
  Arts and Science and Common Services.</p><p>  "These decisions were guid
 ed by several core principles: fulfillment of our academic mission\; a co
 mmitment to centering students and equitable access\; caring for our peop
 le\; advancing the strategic imperatives\; and\, a focus on community eng
 agement and transparency\," President Holmes-Sullivan said in an email se
 nt March 6 to all employees. "While this is a challenging time in CAS and
  Common Services\, it is vital that we come together as a community and m
 ove forward with hope\, compassion and strength."</p>
UID:20260318T210000Z-386456@www.lclark.edu
DTSTAMP:20260310T093159Z
