DESCRIPTION:Professionals across Washington County are invited to invest 
 in their leadership and expand their networks at the 2026 Washington Coun
 ty Women’s Conference & Expo\, presented by Genentech.\n\nBe Called to Le
 ad brings together entrepreneurs\, executives\, and emerging leaders for 
 an afternoon of professional development and meaningful connection. The p
 rogram features a keynote address from Hillsboro Mayor Beach Pace\, netwo
 rking in the Wine Down Lounge\, and opportunities to connect with local b
 usinesses and community partners.\n\nThursday\, March 19\, 2026 12:30 PM 
 – 5:00 PM The Barn at Oakwood Gardens 11785 SW River Rd Hillsboro\, OR 97
 123\n\nThis year’s theme\, Called to Lead: Leadership Rooted in Purpose a
 nd Impact\, focuses on strengthening leadership skills\, building relatio
 nships\, and gaining fresh perspective in today’s business environment.\n
 \nAdmission is $60 early bird or $70 regular. Early bird pricing ends Mar
 ch 1\, and space is limited. Registration includes full conference access
 \, the keynote experience\, one drink ticket\, and light appetizers durin
 g the Wine Down Happy Hour networking reception
