SUMMARY: NW Dance Project: SPRING SONGS
DESCRIPTION:NW Dance Project https://nwdanceproject.org/ presents: Spring
  Songs\n\nMarch 27+28 / 2026 / 7:30 PM at the Newmark Theatre (1111 SW Br
 oadway\, Portland OR 97205)\n\nInfo: https://nwdanceproject.org/performan
 ces https://nwdanceproject.org/performances\n\nTickets: $39+ advance at h
 ttps://app.arts-people.com/index.php?ticketing=nwdp https://app.arts-peop
 le.com/index.php?ticketing=nwdp\n\nAs our spring arrives in Portland\, NW
  Dance Project\, in the throes of its 22nd season\, blooms again with two
  world premiere works from a pair of talented (and friendly) Canadians!\n
 \nNW Dance Project's founding Artistic Director\, Sarah Slipper https://n
 wdanceproject.org/people/sarah-slipper \, creates her latest work for the
  company. An award-winning choreographer noted for her brooding and cinem
 atic works\, Sarah’s new creation is sure to leave a lasting impression a
 nd soak a few hankies.\n\nReturning choreographer and current Choreograph
 ic Associate for The National Ballet of Canada\, Ethan Colangelo https://
 nwdanceproject.org/people/ethan-colangelo \, will create a new work for t
 he company featuring an original score from noted dance music composer Be
 n Waters https://www.benwatersmusic.com/ (not the “British boogie pianist
 ” Ben Waters). Ethan says both creators are "sourcing inspiration from Gu
 stav Mahler’s Symphony No. 5 that encompasses a beautiful dichotomy of lo
 ve/fear\, longing/intimacy\, and hope/anger. In recent years in my own wo
 rk\, I’ve been interested in discovering intersections of contrasting emo
 tional states such as these that have provided immense starting points fo
 r my work. You can expect to see a high level of physical endurance whils
 t also being drawn into an imaginative world exploring human connection a
 nd intimacy."\n\nEstimated full run time is 80 minutes with one 20-minute
  intermission.\n\nCompany Artists info HERE https://nwdanceproject.org/da
 ncers
CATEGORIES:dance,ballet,premiere,Sarah-Slipper
