DESCRIPTION:Reed Zine Fest 2026 is the 3rd annual zine event at Reed Colleg
 e (Kaul Auditorium) brought to you by the Reed Zine and Arts Program throug
 h the Reed College Library. RZF invites over 100+ local community artists a
 nd student zinesters\, keynote speakers\, and free art workshops. This year
 's theme is ZINEWRECKED\, think mermaids\, shipwrecks\, aquatic animals\, o
 cean. Come dressed up on theme! \n\n \n\n11am: RZF Opens! (Kaul Auditorium)
 \n\n12pm-4pm: Art Workshops (Performing Arts Building). Sign up for spots a
 t the Welcome Table in Kaul Auditorium. \n\nDrum Leaf Binding Workshop with
  Sarah Joy Calpo\, 12-1pmComics 2.0 Tips and Tricks Workshop with Marc West
 on\, 1-2pmLet's Day Dream Together: Centering Radical Imagination and Conne
 ction with Envy Estacio\, 3-4pm \n\n12pm-2pm: Mini Keynotes (Performing Art
 s Building). Sign up for spots at the Welcome Table in Kaul Auditorium. \n\
 nZines in the classroom? How to incorporate DIY zines into learning assessm
 ent\, with Professor Megan Brunn (Psychology)Disrupting Institutional Narra
 tives with Archival Research\, with Beq Yonaka \n\n2:30-4:00pm: Keynote Tal
 k with special guest Bre of BrattyxBre (PAB 320)\, a Black and Polynesian a
 rtist based in Long Beach\, California\, and has been creating zines and te
 aching others about zines since 2016. Bre reguarily uploads free zine resou
 rces and tutorials onto her YouTube Channel\, creates exclusive monthly zin
 es for her Zine Club on Patreon\, and spends most weekends selling her zine
 s at in-person events nearby. \n\n4pm: RZF Wraps! \n\n \n\nMore information
  can be found at the Reed Zine Library site or on our Instagram @reedzineli
 brary. This is a masked event (please bring your own KN-95/N-95\, limited a
 mount will be available at the Welcome Table)\, though please note that the
  campus is open to the public and therefore you may encounter non-masked pe
 ople on campus. \n\nThis is a free event\, all ages\, open to the public! P
 lease share this with your friends.
