CREATED:20260225T221411Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260305T205104Z
UID:10000805-1774782000-1774785600@lansugarden.org
SUMMARY:Garden Tea Tastings with Hannah Ma (11 AM)
DESCRIPTION:Overview\n\n\n\nTickets\n\n\n\nTea Master\n\n\n\nParking & Directions\n\n\n\n\nSeries Overview\n\n\n\nThis spring\, take a front-row seat to Chinese tea culture with our intimate Garden Tea Tasting Series (March–May)\, led by tea master Hannah Ma. Savor three seasonal teas from Yun Shui Teahouse\, learn traditional brewing techniques\, and explore the stories behind centuries of tea culture. Your ticket includes admission to Lan Su Chinese Garden on the day of your tasting. \n\n\n\nAfter your 1-hour tasting\, you’ll receive a porcelain teacup to continue your journey at home. All sampled teas will also be available for purchase in our Yun Shui Teahouse. \n\n\n\nFull Series Schedule\n\n\n\nSaturdays & Sundays\, March 21–April 26 | 11:00 AM & 1:00 PM \n\n\n\nFridays & Sundays\, May 1–May 31 | 1:00 PM & 3:00 PM \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nGet Tickets\n\n\n\nSeating is very limited for these intimate group tastings\, so reserve your seat early. Your ticket includes garden admission on the day of your tasting. \n\n\n\n\nLan Su Members & Guests: $36.95\n\n\n\nNon-Members: $55.95\n\n\n\n\nNote: A $0.95 service fee is reflected in each paid ticket \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMeet the Tea Master: Hannah Ma \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nA Portland native\, Hannah grew up drinking tea almost as often as water. Her passion was formally cultivated during her senior year of high school\, when she gained extensive experience with diverse tea blends and preparation techniques as a tea-rista at Portal Tea Company (formerly Tea Chai Té). Now a beverage enthusiast of more than six years\, Hannah is thrilled to join Lan Su’s Tea Tasting program\, where she shares science-based insights into tea’s properties and explores the rich traditions of Chinese-style tea ceremonies. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nParking & Directions\n\n\n\nFree Lan Su Parking\n\n\n\nThere is free first come\, first served parking in our sister lot next to the garden at 424 NW Third Avenue. Additional metered parking and garages are available on surrounding streets.
URL:https://lansugarden.org/event/garden-tea-tasting-11am/2026-03-29/
LOCATION:Lan Su Chinese Garden\, 239 NW Everett Street\, Portland\, Oregon\, 97209
CATEGORIES:Tea
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://lansugarden.org/wp-content/uploads/garden-tea-tastings-hannah-ma-1200x800-1.webp
END:VEVENT
