DESCRIPTION:What do skydiving\, lessons with a professional chef\, perfume 
 making\, and The Lion King broadway show have in common? They are all oppor
 tunities offered to students at Reed by the Gray Fund. The Gray Fund was fo
 unded by the generous benefactor and longtime friend of Reed College\, Bett
 y Gray\, who wanted to ensure that Reed offered stimulating cultural\, soci
 al and recreational programs that complement the academic program and that 
 bring students\, faculty\, and staff together to participate in activities 
 outside of the classroom.\n\nGray Fund events are organized throughout the 
 academic year by the Office for Student Engagement (arts & culture events a
 nd excursions) and Athletics\, Fitness\, and Outdoor Programs (outdoors-foc
 used excursions).\nMembers of the Foster-Scholz Club are invited to Join us
  on March 31 at 3 p.m. PT to hear from students who are part of the team th
 at puts on these events.
