X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p style="font-weight: 400\;">\n  <strong>The Let Out
  is a space which centers on the BIPOC experience at college and how ment
 al health plays a part in this experience. All Lewis and Clark Students a
 re welcome to participate in this space through listening and supporting 
 each other. It is facilitated by one of our on-campus mental health couns
 elors. The counselor is there to guide discussions and answer questions a
 bout mental health challenges while offering ways to cope while at colleg
 e.</strong>\n</p>\n<p style="font-weight: 400\;">\n  <strong><em>So\, if 
 you're needing a space to decompress\, learn new skills\, or talk it out\
 , this is the perfect space to do so. We meet every 1st and 3rd Wednesday
  from 5:30 pm to 6:30 pm\, in Lower Odell\, Room 003</em></strong>\n</p>
