X-SOURCE-ID:reed_college
X-SOURCE:Reed College
CATEGORIES:Student,Workshop/Training,Informational Session
DESCRIPTION:Finding off-campus housing for the first time can be both excit
 ing and overwhelming. This workshop will demystify the process\, answering 
 questions like: "How much should I spend on rent? What should a lease have 
 in it? What should I ask about when looking at a place? What are my rights 
 and responsibilities as a tenant?" and giving you the tools you will need t
 o navigate this life transition. We'll also review resources on and off cam
 pus like Reed Community Pantry and SNAP benefits.\n\nRSVP in Handhake.\n\nT
 his event is organized by The Financial Wellness Group\, a team of students
 \, faculty\, and staff that coordinates new programming about financial wel
 lness and centralizes information about existing resources that support the
  financial wellbeing of students at Reed. \n\nSnacks and beverages provided
  by the Econ Department.
DTEND:20260403T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260312T160904Z
DTSTART:20260402T230000Z
GEO:45.482863;-122.635033
LOCATION:Aspen House\, MPR
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Off-campus Housing Workshop
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50721093852585
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/off-campus-housing-workshop
