CREATED:20260310T215354Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T222155Z
UID:10005657-1775239200-1775246400@literary-arts.org
SUMMARY:Emergency Horse Magazine Launch
DESCRIPTION:The Literary Arts Bookstore & Cafe is pleased to welcome Emergency Horse for the launch of their latest issue. Join us for an evening of readings and celebration. \nThis event is free and open to all. \n\nAbout Emergency Horse \nThe relaunch of the magazine happened this past September. Emergency Horse #8 featured an interview of Robert Hunter\, an article about China’s complicity in the fentanyl scourge\, and another about an artist’s retreat being created on Ken Kesey’s farm. There was an examination of the importance of diversity in society\, and a story about Leprechauns in space. \nOriginally\, the publication existed in the early 1990s with distribution throughout the Northwest and northern California. Back in the day\, the contents featured the irreverent thoughts of the cartoonist Bill Callahan and Allen Ginsberg\, the writing of Charles Bukowski and Lew Welch\, and the advice of the ‘Old Insufferable Car Idiot.’ \nContact: emergencyhorse@gmail.com Attn: Darrin Daniel https://emergencyhorsemagazine.substack.com
URL:https://literary-arts.org/event/emergency-horse-magazine-launch/
LOCATION:Literary Arts
CATEGORIES:Free Events,Bookstore
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://literary-arts.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Emergecy-Horse_600x900-scaled.jpg
GEO:45.5213897;-122.6810304
END:VEVENT
