X-SOURCE-ID:crystal_ballroom
X-SOURCE:Crystal Ballroom
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T200000
DTSTAMP:20260312T090917
CREATED:20251016T173006Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251016T173010Z
UID:10000992-1775332800-1775332800@www.crystalballroompdx.com
SUMMARY:Sticky Fingers
DESCRIPTION:It’s February 2019 and Yours to Keep\, the 4th studio album by the Australian band Sticky Fingers is released. A full tour of the US and Canada was planned in March of the same year…it was half completed\, then cancelled. While the band did perform to thousands of excited fans across the Eastern portion of the US and Canada\, the Western portion never came to be. Ending on March 24th\, 2019\, in Montreal on a frightful and freezing night. The tour finished in a fitting way for Sticky\, no strangers to odd coincidences. \nAfter the show had ended the bands tour bus door was ripped off the hinges. A bus invader came on\, then attempted to run off the bus with a member’s passport and backpack. A tumble ensued\, the invader was pushed off the bus and as the door flew open\, a car driving past clipped it and sent it off the hinges. The unwelcome invader evaded capture\, the door was off\, and the tour was over. \n6.5 years later and Sticky Fingers are coming back to the shores of North America. Fans will rejoice\, guitar strings will be broken\, tears of joy will flow\, fun times are predicted\, and bus doors will remain intact.
URL:https://www.crystalballroompdx.com/events/272238-sticky-fingers/
CATEGORIES:April
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.crystalballroompdx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/StickyFingers0426-g2zmZX.jpg
END:VEVENT
