 .reginawei.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Regina Wei\, LMFT</a></st
 rong> (she/they)\, is an IFS trained therapist in WA with specializations
  in sex therapy and psychedelic assisted therapy (PAT). Their practice pr
 ioritizes folx who identify as BIPOC\, LGBTQIA+\, and/or neurodiverse. Re
 gina's work is informed by a deep commitment to social justice and is foc
 used on healing racial\, intergenerational\, sexual\, and other traumas. 
 Their background includes teaching meditation/mindfulness\, yoga\, and en
 ergy healing in addition to over 15 years of experience in classroom teac
 hing.</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;">  Before working as a therapist\, 
 Regina served for two years as one of the main DEIJ (diversity\, equity\,
  inclusion and justice) practitioners at an independent school where they
  helped facilitate DEIJ conversations among students\, faculty\, and admi
 nistration\, co-led a DEIJ task force\, and was a member of the hiring co
 mmittee for the school's new Director of Equity.&#160\;</p><div id="lw_wi
 dget_470b39ba" class="lw_widget lw_widget_type_blurbs lw_widget_blurbs lw
 _widget_id_3994 lw_widget_opt_in lw_widget_pagination"><ul class="lw_widg
 et_results lw_widget_results_blurbs"><li class="lw_item_1"><div class="lw
 _blurbs_body"><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><em><strong>New workshops and
  trainings are added to our calendar regularly.</strong> For the latest o
 n professional development related to your specific interests\, <a href="
 https://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735441">sign up for our mailing list!</a></e
 m></p></div></li></ul></div>
