 counseling\, school psychology\, and administration in international scho
 ols\, including tips on how to successfully navigate an international lic
 ensed educator job search.  Every candidate who registers with Search Ass
 ociates works with a Senior Associate in one of 23 offices around the wor
 ld. Not a team of strangers or a corporate department\, Search Associates
  staff and consultants have years of experience in international educatio
 n and can provide invaluable guidance and individual assistance throughou
 t the job search.  For more than 30 years\, Search Associates has assiste
 d thousands of teachers\, administrators\, counselors\, librarians\, and 
 interns with finding jobs in hundreds of quality international schools\, 
 and has become the largest and most successful recruitment organization i
 n international education. Currently\, Search Associates works with over 
 750 schools worldwide.  About the PresentersJennifer Imholt\, Senior Asso
 ciate  After graduating from Washington State University with a Bachelor 
 of Arts degree in Communications and Public Relations in 1992\, Jennifer 
 became certified as a K-8 teacher and earned her Master's in Teaching\, w
 ith an emphasis in Curriculum and Instruction at City University in Washi
 ngton. Jennifer has worked as teacher and administrator for 23 years in i
 nternational schools\, including 11 years in South America. Additionally\
 , she has taught in schools in Qatar\, Japan\, Venezuela\, Paraguay\, and
  Colombia. Jennifer has also served as IEP Case Manager (Primary &amp\; E
 lementary)\, at Colegio Nueva Granada's Learning Center in Bogota\, Colom
 bia.Robert Imholt\, Senior Associate  Bob comes to Search Associates with
  an extensive history of leadership experiences gained during his 13-year
 s of military experience as a combat arms officer\, 6-years as executive 
 director at a nonprofit\, and now 22-years of working in international ed
 ucation. As an international educator\, Bob has worked at 6 international
  schools as teacher\, athletic director\, vice-principal\, K-12 principal
 \, middle school principal\, deputy director and director. He was also th
 e director of the International Graduate Program for Educators at Buffalo
  State University\, serving 1\,800 graduate students working at internati
 onal schools around the world. Bob has his Bachelor of Arts and Master's 
 in Teaching from The Evergreen State College\, and his PhD in K-12 Educat
 ional Leadership from Touro University.Jim Albers\, Executive Assistant  
 Jim Albers has been a professional educator for twenty-eight years\, teac
 hing in public\, private and international schools. His international tea
 ching experience includes teaching at The American Embassy School in New 
 Delhi\, India\, and The American International School of Muscat\, Oman. J
 im holds a Bachelor's degree in Education from Washington State Universit
 y and a Master's degree in Educational Administration with Principal's Ce
 rtification from Pacific Lutheran University. Most recently Jim was a mid
 dle school math and geography teacher at Charles Wright Academy in Washin
 gton state. Jim's role includes supporting the marketing and recruiting e
 fforts of the Search Associates' West Coast and Latin America office.New 
 workshops and trainings are added to our calendar regularly. For the late
 st on professional development related to your specific interests\, sign 
 up for our mailing list! (https://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735441)
