X-LIVEWHALE-CONTACT-INFO:<p>\n  Magalí Rabasa\, Director of Ethnic Studi
 es<br />\n  <a href="mailto:mrabasa@lclark.edu">mrabasa@lclark.edu</a>\n<
 /p>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  <span class="a_GcMg font-feature-liga-off font
 -feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-striket
 hrough-none"><span class="a_GcMg font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-
 off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none"><
 em>Ethnic Studies &amp\; Prison Abolition Club Present a Panel Discussion
  with Mapuche Educators<br />\n  <br /></em><strong><span class="a_GcMg f
 ont-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-dec
 oration-none text-strikethrough-none" style="background-color: transparen
 t\;">Indigenous Education for Abolition:</span> <span class="a_GcMg font-
 feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decorat
 ion-none text-strikethrough-none" style="background-color: transparent\;"
 >Mapuche Schools\, Language Revitalization\, and Decolonial Futures<br />
 </span></strong><br />\n  Attacks on Indigenous rights\, public education
 \, and cultural diversity have increased with the rise of fascism in the 
 U.S and Chile. This event explores how Mapuche-run schools and language n
 ests challenge assimilationist state policies and offer lessons for educa
 tors\, students\, and activists in the U.S. grappling with parallel strug
 gles over democracy\, education\, and cultural survival.<br />\n  <br />\
 n  <span style="background-color: transparent\;"><strong><em>This event w
 ill also be available to be viewed on Zoom:</em></strong> <strong><em><a 
 href="https://lclark-edu.zoom.us/j/94410248566">ZOOM LINK</a></em></stron
 g></span><br />\n  <br /></span></span><span class="a_GcMg font-feature-l
 iga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none 
 text-strikethrough-none">—<br /></span>\n</p>\n<p>\n  <strong>Educació
 n Indígena para la abolición de la cárcel: escuelas mapuche\, revitali
 zación lingüística y futuros decoloniales</strong>\n</p>\n<p>\n  Los a
 taques a los derechos indígenas\, la educación pública y la diversidad
  cultural han aumentado con el auge del fascismo en Estados Unidos y Chil
 e. Este evento habla acerca de cómo las escuelas y los nidos lingüísti
 cos mapuche desafían las políticas estatales asimilacionistas y ofrece 
 lecciones para educadores\, estudiantes y activistas en Estados Unidos qu
 e lidian con luchas paralelas por la democracia\, la educación y la supe
 rvivencia cultural.<br />\n  <br />\n  <span class="a_GcMg font-feature-l
 iga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none 
 text-strikethrough-none"><strong><em>Este evento también estará present
 ado por Zoom:</em></strong> <strong><em><a href="https://lclark-edu.zoom.
 us/j/94410248566" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ZOOM LINK</a></em></stro
 ng></span>\n</p>\n<p>\n  <span class="a_GcMg font-feature-liga-off font-f
 eature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethr
 ough-none"><span class="a_GcMg font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-of
 f font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none">&#1
 60\;</span></span>\n</p>
END:VEVENT
