SUMMARY:EndNote Basics
DESCRIPTION:EndNote is a popular reference management tool at OHSU. Sign up 
 for this hands-on workshop to learn how to use it!\n\nWe will 
 cover:\n\n\n	How to build and organize an EndNote Library\n	How to use 
 EndNote to find full text PDFs for articles via the OHSU Library 
 Catalog\n	How to use the EndNote Add-in for Microsoft Word to create and 
 format citations and bibliographies\n\n\nPrerequisites:\n\n\n	Please visit 
 our Citation and Reference Management Guide to download and install the 
 site-licensed EndNote desktop client before the workshop begins\n	Make sure 
 you have Microsoft Word installed\n\n\nPlease note:\n\n\n	Because OHSU's 
 EndNote site license is limited to OHSU Members\, this workshop is limited 
 to OHSU Members only\, and you will need to log in with your OHSU 
 credentials to register\n
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="OHSU Library":MAILTO:library@ohsu.libanswers.com
CATEGORIES:Citation and Reference Management
