SUMMARY: Mozart's "Così fan tutte" by PSU Opera
DESCRIPTION:Romance\, intrigue\, trickery and a risky wager are at the he
 art of Mozart’s comical opera “Così fan tutte” (Italian for “They all do 
 it”). In this darkly comedic opera buffo\, presented by Portland State Un
 iversity’s award-winning opera program\, the cynical mastermind Don Alfon
 so makes a bet with two young men\, Ferrando and Guglielmo\, that their d
 evoted fiancées\, Dorabella and Fiordiligi\, will prove unfaithful if tem
 ptation is put in their path. Fully believing in the women’s steadfast lo
 yalty\, the young men accept the bet. With the help of the shrewd maid De
 spina\, Don Alfonso manipulates the quartet in an elaborate deception\, d
 isguising the men as ardent suitors and orchestrating a series of hijinks
  that would weaken the resolve of even the truest love. Through the magic
  of Mozart’s sparkling score\, combining sublime vocal ensembles with sha
 rp comedy\, the opera explores timeless questions about love\, loyalty\, 
 and the unpredictability of the human heart.\n\nWill the two young women 
 remain faithful to their fiances\, or will they be tricked into betraying
  them\, revealing their all-too-human frailty? Join PSU Opera April 17 th
 rough 26 to find out!\n\nPerformances include a pre-performance lecture o
 ne hour prior and are accompanied by a full\, live orchestra.
CATEGORIES:theater,opera,classical-music,live-music
