SUMMARY:AI as Collaborator
DESCRIPTION:AI as Collaborator Workshop Part 1: The Creative SparkDuratio
 n: 1 HourLocation: Google Meet (Register (https://docs.google.com/forms/d
 /e/1FAIpQLSd9ZO3fZCVD6c-Bmne4iMRUXyoVINidkRWNAjXjAsGhvBD5Xw/viewform?usp=
 header) for calendar invite)Description:  Move beyond using AI as just a 
 "vending machine" (input -&gt\; output) and learn to use it as a collabor
 ative thought partner. In the first session of our two-part series\, we w
 ill focus on Divergent Thinking—using AI to overcome writer's block\, g
 enerate creative ideas\, and expand your strategic thinking.What we will 
 cover:The Mindset Shift: Moving from "Directive" to "Collaborative."    T
 he Coach Persona: How to get AI to help you outline and strategize.    Th
 e Muse Persona: Generating volume\, variety\, and creative angles.    Liv
 e Demos: Bring your laptop! We will be running live experiments.      AI 
 as Collaborator Workshop Part 2: The Critical LensDuration: 1 HourLocatio
 n: Google MeetDescription: In Part 2\, we learn how to refine our ideas. 
 This session focuses on Convergent Thinking—using AI to stress-test you
 r logic\, polish your tone\, and simulate audience reactions before you h
 it "send."What we will cover:The Editor Persona: rewriting for tone\, cla
 rity\, and impact.    The Devil's Advocate: Using AI to find holes in you
 r logic and risks in your plan.    The Virtual Focus Group: Simulating st
 akeholders (students\, admin\, skeptics) to prep for difficult questions.
     Pre-work: Please bring one "Ugly Draft" (an email\, policy\, or propo
 sal that is unfinished or rough). We will use the tools to polish it live
  during the session.
