X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Portland Community College": "https://events.pcc.edu/event/10060-the-resilience-resource-collective"}
X-SOURCE-ID:portland_community_college
X-SOURCE:Portland Community College
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260421T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260421T124500
SUMMARY:The Resilience & Resource Collective
DESCRIPTION:"The Resilience &amp\; Resource CollectiveA Peer-to-Peer Shar
 ing CircleApril 14\, 21\, and 2812:00 to 12:45In person: Southeast Mt Tab
 or Hall room 100Virtual via Zoom at https://portlandcc.zoom.us/j/96697103
 029?pwd=kCGXBO72hfCQjIoWk4vNQlEXgPj7St.1 (https://portlandcc.zoom.us/j/96
 697103029?pwd=kCGXBO72hfCQjIoWk4vNQlEXgPj7St.1)The Student Basic Needs Ce
 nter invites you to join the Resilience &amp\; Resource Collective\, a st
 udent-led group focused on housing\, finances\, and mental health. Listen
 ing counts. No shame. No fixing. Just collective wisdom and practical res
 ources.Across three sessions\, we'll demystify housing systems\, share co
 llege funding strategies\, and reflect on what helped us get through the 
 year. This is not a lecture\, it's a peer resource-sharing space grounded
  in mutual aid and lived experience.No registration required\, attend any
  or all sessions\, in-person or online. Questions? Email basicneeds@pcc.e
 du "—Event Details: https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp?id=382426 (https://hub.pcc
 .edu/rsvp?id=382426)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:"The Resilience &amp\; Resource Collective<b
 r />A Peer-to-Peer Sharing Circle<br />April 14\, 21\, and 28<br />12:00 
 to 12:45<br />In person: Southeast Mt Tabor Hall room 100<br />Virtual vi
 a Zoom at <a href="https://portlandcc.zoom.us/j/96697103029?pwd=kCGXBO72h
