X-LIVEWHALE-CONTACT-INFO:<p>Questions? Contact <a href="mailto:leadserve@
 lclark.edu">leadserve@lclark.edu</a>&#160\;</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>Interested in a mentorship opportunity? Sign up to
  volunteer with the Center for Social Change as we welcome a group of 3rd
  graders and future scholars from Alder Elementary School. Lead a campus 
 tour and/or host an interactive activity to give a students a glimpse of 
 college life. BIPOC and/or Spanish speaking students encouraged to sign u
 p! Multiple shifts will be available for this event. There is some flexib
 ility around shift timing and roles available. The general time commitmen
 t is expected to be around 2 hours. Please note that there will be a 30-m
 inute volunteer training the week of the event.<br />\n<br />\nShift 1: 9
 :40am-11:30am<br />\nShift 2: 11:20am-1:00pm<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Choos
 e one of two volunteer roles for this event:</strong><br />\n<br />\n<str
 ong>Tour Leader:</strong> Show students around campus and take them to ac
 tivity areas for a scavenger hunt. Share your educational journey\, educa
 te the students on the history of Lewis &amp\; Clark\, and answer general
  questions from the kids.<br />\n<strong>Activity Leader:</strong> Help t
 he students engage in a scavenger hunt across different sites on campus\,
