X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Portland Fun Run": "https://www.meetup.com/portland-fun-run/events/wxqxvtyjcgbdc/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_portland_fun_run
X-SOURCE:Meetup Portland Fun Run
UID:event_wxqxvtyjcgbdc@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260312T160928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T220000
SUMMARY:Run & Chug!
DESCRIPTION:Portland Fun Run\nThe route will be posted soon! In the meantime\, here are some FAQs:\n\n**Where do I find the group?**\nWe typically meet up right outside the bar! We rotate through a variety of bars and breweries. Check out our past events to see what places we typically go to.\n\n**What is the average pace of the group?**\nThere is a wide range of paces that varies week-to-week\, but typically most people are between 7:30 - 10 minute miles. We welcome all runners\, regardless of pace (the #1 goal our group is to make new friends\, not break records)\, but we advise making sure you are comfortable with the route if you are worried you might be slower than this range\, just so you don’t get lost.\n\n**What time does the group actually start running?**\nWe suggest runners arrive around 6:55pm\, but we do not actually start running until 7:05pm.\n\n**When is the route posted?**\nThe route is posted typically Tuesday night or Wednesday morning.\nI don’t have a car\, what do I do with my belongings while I’m running?\nOne option is to wear a running belt to keep keys\, ID\, credit card\, etc. on you while you run\, but if you show up a little early\, you can often find someone who is willing to put your jacket or other belongings in their car for you during the run.\n\n**What should I bring?**\nMake sure to bring your ID and credit card/cash for the bar. Additionally\, in the winter\, we recommend bringing a light to run with and wearing something reflective. Lastly\, we are sometimes outside for drinks\, depending on the location\, so it’s a good idea to bring a jacket.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/portland-fun-run/events/wxqxvtyjcgbdc/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260204T224959Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260204T224959Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/a/6/1/600_503363137.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ohsu Library": "https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/event/16554354"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ohsu_library
X-SOURCE:Ohsu Library
DTSTART:20260422T190000Z
DTEND:20260422T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260422T000000Z
SUMMARY:Kickstart Your Writing With AI
DESCRIPTION:Staring at a blank page? This workshop will teach you how to 
 use generative AI tools (such as ChatGPT) to get started with your 
 writing\, ethically and effectively! \n\nThis workshop is designed for 
 students in any program. The learning outcomes include: \n\n\n	\n	Writing 
 effective prompts for GenAI tools \n	\n\n\n\n	\n	Finding trustworthy 
 background information with GenAI \n	\n\n\n\n	\n	Using GenAI in the early 
 stages of the writing process to create outlines\, break down complex 
 tasks\, and more \n	\n\n\n\n	\n	Avoiding plagiarism and citing GenAI 
 appropriately \n	\n\n\n\n	\n	Using GenAI in accordance with journal 
 policies \n	\n\n\nThis workshop will be recorded\, and the recording will 
 be shared with all registered attendees after the session. If you cannot 
 make the workshop date and time\, you are welcome to register in order to 
 receive a copy of the recording.
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Tova Johnson":MAILTO:johnstov@ohsu.edu
CATEGORIES:AI
UID:LibCal-6248-16554354
URL:https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/event/16554354
END:VEVENT
