X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lewis Clark": "https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/event/371141-where-should-moral-philosophy-begin-by-avram-hiller-p"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lewis_clark
X-SOURCE:Lewis Clark
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T163000
LOCATION:J.R. Howard Hall 202
GEO:45.451619;-122.669391
SUMMARY:Where Should Moral Philosophy Begin? by Avram Hiller (Portland St
 ate University)
UID:20260424T223000Z-371141@www.lclark.edu
DTSTAMP:20250922T125739Z
URL:https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/event/371141-where-should-mor
 al-philosophy-begin-by-avram-hiller-p
CATEGORIES:Open to the Public
LAST-MODIFIED:20260203T165541Z
ATTACH:https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/77/width/80/height/80/crop/1
 /src_region/0,0,225,225/109881_Avram_Hiller_.rev.1758570918.jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-TYPE:events
X-LIVEWHALE-ID:371141
X-LIVEWHALE-TIMEZONE:America/Los_Angeles
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE:https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/77/width/80/heigh
 t/80/crop/1/src_region/0\,0\,225\,225/109881_Avram_Hiller_.rev.1758570918
 .jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE-CAPTION:Avram Hiller
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  How should one live? Why be moral? These quest
 ions are commonly used as the points of departure for moral theorizing. A
 lthough they are of course deeply important\, I argue that they misdirect
  moral theory. First\, they focus primarily on agents—ones who act—ra
 ther than those who are acted upon. Second\, they concern agents as indiv
 iduals rather than collectives. I discuss how the individualistic agent-c
 entered approach has had a distorting effect on moral theory\, and propos
 e an alternative methodology focusing on those affected by actions and in
 stitutions.<br />\n  <br />\n  3:30-5:00PM PST\n</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-TAGS:faculty event|faculty|open to the public|philosophy coll
 oquium series|Philosophy Major|philosophy minor|send-to-undergraduate|stu
 dent event|student
END:VEVENT
