X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lewis Clark": "https://www.lclark.edu/live/events/381620-music-colloquium-dr-kerry-mccarthy"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lewis_clark
X-SOURCE:Lewis Clark
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T180000
LOCATION:Evans Auditorium
GEO:45.452273;-122.669241
SUMMARY:Music Colloquium: Dr. Kerry McCarthy
DESCRIPTION:Tudor Singers on the Road  We hear a lot about Renaissance co
 mposers\, but Dr. Kerry McCarthy will talk about the people who actually 
 sang their music and brought it to life\, sometimes in quite challenging 
 circumstances\, and how touring as a musician with Henry VIII wasn't all 
 that different from touring with Taylor Swift!Kerry McCarthy is a musicia
 n and author who has published widely on the English Renaissance\, includ
 ing award-winning new biographies of the composers William Byrd and Thoma
 s Tallis. She is now writing her fourth book\, an exploration of the live
 s of professional singers in Tudor England. She lives in Portland\, where
  she was born and raised.  &#160\;Parking at Lewis &amp\; Clark - For eve
 nts in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion
 \, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswold\, Lower Griswold\, or Fir A
 cres Lots (see: campus map (https://www.lclark.edu/live/files/7676-campus
 -map)).Parking permits are required during the academic year between Mond
 ay through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see the Visiting Campus page (http
 s://www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transportation/visitor_parking/) for
  additional details. For weekday events before 7pm\, visitors may purchas
 e day passes online (https://lclark.t2hosted.com/Account/Portal) or via Q
 R codes posted in all major parking lots.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Tudor Singers on the Road</strong
 ></p><p>  We hear a lot about Renaissance composers\, but Dr. Kerry McCar
 thy will talk about the people who actually sang their music and brought 
 it to life\, sometimes in quite challenging circumstances\, and how touri
 ng as a musician with Henry VIII wasn't all that different from touring w
 ith Taylor Swift!</p><p><span data-sheets-root="1"><picture class="lw_ima
 ge lw_image111625  lw_align_left"><source type="image/webp" srcset="https
 ://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/76/width/200/height/221/111625_
 McCarthy_-_Kerry_McCarthy.webp 2x" data-origin="responsive"/><source type
 ="image/jpeg" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/76/w
 idth/200/height/221/111625_McCarthy_-_Kerry_McCarthy.rev.1769557142.jpg 2
 x" data-origin="responsive"/><img width="200" height="221" alt="" data-al
 t="" data-decoration="true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/76
 /width/200/height/221/111625_McCarthy_-_Kerry_McCarthy.rev.1769557142.jpg
 " title="McCarthy - Kerry McCarthy" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/i
 mage/scale/2x/gid/76/width/200/height/221/111625_McCarthy_-_Kerry_McCarth
 y.rev.1769557142.jpg 2x" data-max-w="578" data-max-h="640" loading="lazy"
  data-optimized="true"/></picture>Kerry McCarthy is a musician and author
  who has published widely on the English Renaissance\, including award-wi
 nning new biographies of the composers William Byrd and Thomas Tallis. Sh
 e is now writing her fourth book\, an exploration of the lives of profess
 ional singers in Tudor England. She lives in Portland\, where she was bor
 n and raised.</span></p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Parking at Lewis &amp\
 ; Clark</strong> - <em>For events in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Ch
 apel\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion\, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswo
 ld\, Lower Griswold\, or Fir Acres Lots (see: <a href="https://www.lclark
 .edu/live/files/7676-campus-map" target="_blank" rel="noopener">campus ma
 p</a>).</em><em>Parking permits are required during the academic year bet
 ween Monday through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see the <a href="https://
 www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transportation/visitor_parking/">Visitin
 g Campus page</a> for additional details. For weekday events before 7pm\,
  visitors may purchase day passes <a href="https://lclark.t2hosted.com/Ac
 count/Portal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">online</a> or via QR codes p
 osted in all major parking lots.</em></p>
