CATEGORIES:Alumni
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to make artisinal bon bons in Georgetown! \n\nWill Hu
 iras '14 has been moonlighting under internationally renown chocolatier Ana
 bella Arcay of Arcay Chocolates—and it's come time to share all that's been
  learned! Learn painting\, molding\, filling\, and everything else involved
  in the creation of artisanal bon bons.\n\nPrecautions: wear kitchen safe a
 ttire that you don't mind being covered in chocolate\; consider bringing a 
 mask if sensitive to aerosolized particles\; this will be hands on\, standi
 ng for a couple hours.\n\nThe kitchen can support 4-5 people at a time\, if
  there is a large interest we can do multiple sessions.\n\nThis event is he
 avily dependant on RSVPs\, which will inform number of sessions\, the cost 
 to the college and the cost to you. RSVP by 4/11. Stay tuned for an RSVP li
 nk.
