SUMMARY:Indian Music Ensemble Performance
DESCRIPTION:The goals of this ensemble include learning foundational elem
 ents of North Indian Classical Music pedagogy and theory\, as well as the
  unique\, non-musical aspects of the form. This group finds creative ways
  of expression combining Indian Classical forms with the broad language o
 f contemporary musical lexicon\, all while having fun!  &#160\;Parking at
  Lewis &amp\; Clark - For events in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Cha
 pel\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion\, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswol
 d\, Lower Griswold\, or Fir Acres Lots (see: campus map (https://www.lcla
 rk.edu/live/files/7676-campus-map)).Parking permits are required during t
 he academic year between Monday through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see t
 he Visiting Campus page (https://www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transpo
 rtation/visitor_parking/) for additional details. For weekday events befo
 re 7pm\, visitors may purchase day passes online (https://lclark.t2hosted
 .com/Account/Portal) or via QR codes posted in all major parking lots.
