BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Reed College": "https://events.reed.edu/event/copy-of-denim-day"}
X-SOURCE-ID:reed_college
X-SOURCE:Reed College
CATEGORIES:Social,Tabling
DESCRIPTION:Denim Day is a campaign on a Wednesday in April where folks wea
 r denim to demonstrate support for survivors and challenge myths supporting
  sexual violence. The campaign began after a ruling by the Italian Supreme 
 Court in 1999\, where a rape conviction was overturned after the judges rul
 ed that the jeans worn by the victim were too tight to not have been remove
 d by the victim–thereby implying consent. The day following the ruling\, wo
 men in the Italian Parliament came to work wearing jeans in solidarity with
  the victim. \n\nCome by our table outside the GCC to add your patch to our
  Denim Quilt and show your allied support for survivors.
DTEND:20260429T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260312T160905Z
