 red therapy rooted in compassion and unconditional positive regard. She h
 as specialized training in trauma-informed counseling\, mindfulness\, and
  body-based therapies. Julianna is registered with Yoga Alliance as RYT 5
 00-hr and is excited by the collective considerations of how we can embra
 ce ancient practices from other cultures with ethical\, conscious care. S
 he teaches graduate classes as an adjunct faculty member at the Lewis &am
 p\; Clark Graduate School in the Counseling Program\, and offers training
 s for clinicians in trauma informed embodiment practices to inform ethica
