 Salem\, OR. She received her MFA in Painting at University of Wisconsin\,
  Madison and has shown her work in venues including the Whatcom Museum (B
 ellingham\, WA)\, the University of Minnesota's Nash Gallery (Minneapolis
 \, MN)\, Boise State University (Boise\, ID)\, and Overture Center for th
 e Arts (Madison\, WI). Her work invites viewers to reimagine their relati
 onship with the natural world\, reignite a sense of wonder\, and advocate
  for environmental care through the language of paint.Her work has appear
 ed in publications such as <em>The Bear Deluxe</em> and <em>Tree Sap Maga
 zine</em>. Larson is a past artist in residence at Caldera (Sisters\, Ore
 gon)\, New Pacific Studios (Masterton\, New Zealand)\, and Fish Factory C
 reative Centre of Stöðvarfjörður (Iceland). When not in the studio\, 
 she teaches at Clark College and is the Archer Gallery and Clark Art Talk
 s Director. She is represented by Augen Gallery in Portland\, OR and AMcE
  Creative Arts in Seattle\, WA.&#160\;</p><div id="lw_widget_470b39ba" cl
